          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 24x8x48 cm3 prototype detector consisting of",
                "9216 1 cm scintillator cubes, exposed to the neutron",
                "beam. Each energy deposit signal in a cube was",
                "collected by three WLS fibers and mapped in three",
                "orthogonal views. The detector used three types of",
                "Hamamatsu MP-PCs, S13360-1325CS, S13081-050CS and",
                "S12571-025C, installed in three different regions of",
                "the top view of the detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Plastic scintillator (CH)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRN",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The total neutron cross-section measurement",
                "was estimated utilizing the so-called extinction",
                "technique. In the presence of neutron-nucleus",
                "interactions, the signal event rate decreases",
                "exponentially along the z-coordinate: N(z) = N0*exp(-",
                "T*sigmatot*z), where N0 and N(z) are the neutron",
                "event rates at the reconstructed z positions in the",
                "first layer, and in a more downstream layer in the",
                "detector. T and sigmatot are the nuclear density and",
                "the neutron total cross section, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The total uncertainty is dominated by the",
                "contribution from the detection systematic",
                "uncertainty. The detector has a geometrical and",
                "electronics non-uniformity which generates a",
                "detection uncertainty. The fiber, fiber hole, MPPC,",
                "insulating Tyvek layer and cubes have some variation",
                "in their alignment."
              ]
            },
